Modelos de regresión: Base de datos con todos los casos

#data %>% group_by(Sexo) %>% skim(igualdad.est)

Modelo nulo

data$RBD <- as.factor(data$RBD)

reg0_igualdad <- lme4::lmer(igualdad.est ~ 1 + (1 | RBD), data=data)
reg0_pub <- lme4::lmer(esp_publico.est ~ 1 + (1 | RBD), data=data)
reg0_priv <- lme4::lmer(esp_privado.est ~ 1 + (1 | RBD), data=data)

stargazer::stargazer(reg0_igualdad, reg0_pub, reg0_priv,
  column.labels=c("Igualdad","Espacio público", "Espacio privado"),
  type ='text')
## 
## ================================================================
##                                 Dependent variable:             
##                     --------------------------------------------
##                     igualdad.est esp_publico.est esp_privado.est
##                       Igualdad   Espacio público Espacio privado
##                         (1)            (2)             (3)      
## ----------------------------------------------------------------
## Constant               -0.028        -0.030          -0.031     
##                       (0.028)        (0.033)         (0.037)    
##                                                                 
## ----------------------------------------------------------------
## Observations           1,615          1,615           1,615     
## Log Likelihood       -1,053.727    -1,183.792      -1,412.776   
## Akaike Inf. Crit.    2,113.454      2,373.585       2,831.552   
## Bayesian Inf. Crit.  2,129.615      2,389.746       2,847.714   
## ================================================================
## Note:                                *p<0.1; **p<0.05; ***p<0.01
screenreg(list(reg0_igualdad, reg0_pub, reg0_priv))
## 
## =====================================================
##                       Model 1    Model 2    Model 3  
## -----------------------------------------------------
## (Intercept)              -0.03      -0.03      -0.03 
##                          (0.03)     (0.03)     (0.04)
## -----------------------------------------------------
## AIC                    2113.45    2373.58    2831.55 
## BIC                    2129.62    2389.75    2847.71 
## Log Likelihood        -1053.73   -1183.79   -1412.78 
## Num. obs.              1615       1615       1615    
## Num. groups: RBD         64         64         64    
## Var: RBD (Intercept)      0.04       0.06       0.07 
## Var: Residual             0.20       0.23       0.31
